      "writtenOn": "2026-03-18T20:54:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You should only use std::move() on objects of a class that contain resources and that you want to take ownership of or steal the resources from.\n\nFor gpioPins, this is correct because the parameter is by copy (no reference) and contains unique_ptrs (which cannot be copied without move). So you want to std::move a container of unique_ptrs that you are taking ownership of.\n\nSimilarly, presencePath is by copy (no reference), so it is smart to std::move it since you can steal the memory of the contained std::string.\n\nFor built-in types (int, float, bool, etc) and objects that you are not taking ownership of (such as a const std::string\u0026), you don\u0027t need/want to to std::move().",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 68,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 68,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "a903d190c95de60b41a0630cd390e23c930cca4b",
